cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.Distributed Systems. 

The paper discusses a self-organizing solution for maintaining multicast trees in distributed systems, which involves network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions the use of traditional distributed systems techniques, layering, soft-state, and passive data collection, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the ability of the system to adapt to network changes and recover from failures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as well. Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the system on a testbed and emulated networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.Distributed Systems.
